e on new meanings, that are also central for architecture. Today the use of generative computerized methods is opening up new ways of talking about an idea that is becoming increasingly abstract and dynamic. Pattern explores the question: what are the notions of pattern that must be discussed in the context of contemporary architecture?  aComplex patterns are founded on simple rules. Pattern and pattern formation are of new, important significance as the fundamental principles of systematization and description of very complex processes and phenomena. Which idea of pattern has to be used in the architectural discourse today?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aArchitectural theory. 4aArt. 4aCAAD. 4aComplexity. 4aCultural studies. 4aDesign. 4aMedia sciences. 4aPattern formation. 4aPattern language. 4aTheory and philosophy of technology. 7aARCHITECTURE / History / General.2bisacsh1 aChristen, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGleiniger, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGleiniger, Andrea, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGleiniger, Andrea.1 aHölscher, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMundry, Isabel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScheurer, Fabian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVrachliotis, Georg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVrachliotis, Georg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVrachliotis, Georg.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Art and Architecture 200